{
  "id": "a95a1e4c4317c900",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/skelar/c8247032-9d7a-45d6-837c-762a5b8f4d73/application",
    "company": "skelar",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "a95a1e4c4317c900",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/3a2721ac-0cf6-4bb5-a785-483b8d1018c3/Ashby_header.png]\n\nSKELAR is a venture builder that creates international IT companies according to venture capital investment guidelines. Together with our co-founders, we assemble solid and efficient teams to launch tech businesses that will succeed globally.\n\nToday, SKELAR brings together a dozen businesses across various niches — from EdTech to marketplaces. These are companies featured in Ukraine’s top startup and product company rankings, leading the App Store charts, and building platforms used by millions of people. SKELAR’s businesses have also been mentioned by global media such as TechCrunch, Wired, and others.\n\nWe’re proud of our strong team of 1,000+ professionals with exceptional expertise and ambitious goals. Our people are the company’s most valuable asset, which is why we choose to build businesses together with the best talent on the market.\n\n﻿We are currently looking for Content Manager (Beauty Tech) to join MaxBeauty.\n\nMaxBeauty brings together a team of ambitious people striving to revolutionize the world of self-care and become a leader in the international beauty \u0026 wellness market.\n\nOur mission is to make people happy through self-care and self-love, which is why we’re creating an ecosystem of products designed to be lovel by millions of users. Right now, we’re focused on developing our core product — a personal self-care assistant powered by proven methods, expert knowledge, and AI technologies.\n\nYou’ll have a unique opportunity to join an experienced team in an early-stage business that has already found its unit economics, is scaling, and still offers plenty of room for vertical growth. This is a place where you can have a direct impact on the business, bring your own ideas to life, and grow in proportion to your contribution — not within predefined limits or bureaucratic structures.\n\nIn this role you will:\n\n - Create and manage educational beauty and wellness content, including lessons, courses, in-app materials, and AI-generated video lessons and visual content using modern AI\n\n - Track and analyze content performance metrics (engagement, completion rates, retention impact, etc.)\n\n - Run content experiments to continuously improve effectiveness and drive measurable results\n\n - Write clear, engaging scripts for educational video content\n\n - Ensure all content is accurate, user-friendly, and aligned with the brand voice and content standards\n\n - Manage, upload, and update content using CMS and LMS platforms\n\n - Review, edit, and improve existing content to maintain high quality and relevance\n\n - Research beauty, skincare, and wellness topics to support content creation\n\n - Stay informed about beauty industry trends, user needs, and emerging topics\n\n - Collaborate with product, design, and cross-functional teams to support content initiatives\n\nWhat is important for us:\n\n - English proficiency at B2+ level (Upper-Intermediate) or higher\n\n - Strong writing, editing, and proofreading skills\n\n - Experience creating instructional and educational content (both long-form and short-form)\n\n - Ability to develop and adapt tone of voice according to brand guidelines\n\n - Ability to write scripts for educational or instructional video content\n\n - Experience working with CMS and/or LMS platforms\n\n - Strong attention to detail and commitment to content quality\n\n - Ability to work with AI tools (e.g., ChatGPT, ElevenLabs, Gemini)\n\n - Strong research skills and ability to fact-check information\n\n - Solid grasp of content performance metrics, ability to work with analytics tools (e.g., Amplitude) and user feedback sources\n\n - Data-driven approach to decision making\n\nBonus points for:\n\n - You are fluent in beauty and skincare trends\n\n - Understanding of beauty apps and digital product environments\n\n - Interest in beauty market research and industry trends\n\n - You’ve lived in English-speaking countries\n\n - Experience working with educational, wellness, or app-based content / experience in education\n\n - Proficiency in either French, German, Spanish, Portuguese, Japanese Knowledge of additional languages such as French, German, Portuguese, or Japanese will be a strong advantage\n\nYou will be a great fit and enjoy this role if you are:\n\n - Act proactively and take initiative\n\n - Love a structured, systematic approach to problem-solving\n\n - Ambitious, results-oriented person who is driven by results and achievements\n\n - Genuinely interested in Health, Beauty, and Wellness niches, who want to deeply understand the audience and can spot and create trends\n\nWhat to expect:\n\n - Competitive, market-aligned compensation\n\n - A strong, experienced, and highly motivated team\n\n - Unlimited opportunities for professional growth and networking\n\n - Asymmetric career growth opportunities\n\n - Full remote work setup\n\nMaxBeauty is backed by SKELAR, a venture builder with over 10 successful B2C businesses in its portfolio. SKELAR provides access to the best payment infrastructure for our business model, along with financial and legal support in our target locations. They also organize internal clubs focused on professional development in marketing, development, and payments. With SKELAR, there’s always someone to turn to for advice or assistance.\n\nBeyond business, SKELAR builds the SKELAR Foundation, a charitable initiative created by employees. Through this initiative, we create and fund large projects that help bring us closer to victory.\n\nJoin us in building the next big thing!\n\n[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/bf8afb62-59f5-436b-b500-74f06bd0bb6e/Ashby_footer_eng.png]",
